soot.jimple.infoflow.entryPointCreators

Class AndroidEntryPointCreator

  • java.lang.Object
    • soot.jimple.infoflow.entryPointCreators.BaseEntryPointCreator
      • soot.jimple.infoflow.entryPointCreators.AndroidEntryPointCreator
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    IEntryPointCreator

    public class AndroidEntryPointCreator
extends BaseEntryPointCreator
implements IEntryPointCreator
    class which creates a dummy main method with the entry points according to the Android lifecycles based on: http://developer.android.com/reference/android/app/Activity.html#ActivityLifecycle and http://developer.android.com/reference/android/app/Service.html and http://developer.android.com/reference/android/content/BroadcastReceiver.html#ReceiverLifecycle and http://developer.android.com/reference/android/content/BroadcastReceiver.html
    Author:
    Christian, Steven Arzt

      • componentTypeCache

        private java.util.Map<soot.SootClass,AndroidEntryPointCreator.ComponentType> componentTypeCache
        Soot requires a main method, so we create a dummy method which calls all entry functions. Android's components are detected and treated according to their lifecycles. This method automatically resolves the classes containing the given methods.

      • addCallbackMethods

        private boolean addCallbackMethods(soot.SootClass currentClass)
        Generates invocation statements for all callback methods which need to be invoked during the given class' run cycle.
        Parameters:
        currentClass - The class for which we currently build the lifecycle
        Returns:

      • addCallbackMethods

        private boolean addCallbackMethods(soot.SootClass currentClass,
                                   java.util.Set<soot.SootClass> referenceClasses,
                                   java.lang.String callbackSignature)
        Generates invocation statements for all callback methods which need to be invoked during the given class' run cycle.
        Parameters:
        currentClass - The class for which we currently build the lifecycle
        referenceClasses - The classes for which no new instances shall be created, but rather existing ones shall be used.
        callbackSignature - An empty string if calls to all callback methods for the given class shall be generated, otherwise the subsignature of the only callback method to generate.
        Returns:
        True if a matching callback has been found, otherwise false.
